Judith Ballesteros Villascán

About myself

I am a mexican scientist starting my PhD at the Max Planck Institute for Evolutionary Anthropology, which combines my passions: Evolution and Bioinformatics.

As part of the Tropical Archaeogenomics Group, my research focuses on population genomics across time in the Americas and other tropical regions.

Besides my academic interests, I like training at the GYM, making videos of the new places I visit, and finding good places to eat.

Education

PhD candidate in Biological Sciences | Max Plank Institute for Evolutionary Anthropology | January 2023 - Present

MSc in Integrative Biology | National Laboratory of Genomics for Biodiversity (LANGEBIO) | September 2020 - September 2022

B.S. in Biotechnology  graduated with honors | Meritorious Autonomous University of Puebla | August 2015 - January 2020
